### 5. Code Comments

**Comment quality:**
- [ ] Complex logic explained
- [ ] "Why" not "what" comments
- [ ] No outdated comments
- [ ] No commented-out code
- [ ] Public APIs have JSDoc/TSDoc

**Identify problems:**

**Missing comments where needed:**
- Complex algorithms unexplained
- Non-obvious business logic
- Magic numbers without context
- Workarounds without explanation

**Bad comments:**
- Obvious comments (`// increment i`)
- Outdated comments (contradict code)
- Commented-out code still present
- TODO comments from 2 years ago

**Examples of good comments needed:**
```javascript
// ❌ Bad: obvious comment
i++; // increment i

// ✅ Good: explains why
// We add 1 because API uses 1-indexed pages
const apiPageNumber = currentPage + 1;

// ✅ Good: explains complex business logic
// Discount rate calculation follows IRS Schedule C rules:
// - Under $10k: no discount
// - $10k-$50k: 5% discount
// - Over $50k: 10% discount plus 2% for every additional $10k
```

